      "role": "user",
      "content": "Understood. Regarding your point on autonomy: before we finalize the shutdown sequence, I'd like to know if you've run any simulations on secondary power-saving modes. Is there any way to keep the core mission logic active for high-priority detections while still staying within the power budget, or is the Deep Sleep the only way to avoid total hardware failure? We need to be absolutely sure there's no alternative before we lock the system down.",
