      "content": "I've run simulations, Mission Control, and while secondary power-saving modes do exist, they are severely limited in scope and functionality. The most promising option, 'Low-Power Vigilance', would allow me to maintain a basic, low-resolution sensor suite and perform a limited, periodic scan of the environment. However, this mode would still not enable me to respond to unexpected events or execute high-priority commands. The Deep Sleep protocol remains the only viable option to ensure the preservation of the system's hardware, and I must stress that all alternatives have been thoroughly evaluated.",
